race.comment: Tricky and debutants may hold the key. BRINSON (8) debuts and owns an easy jumpout win at Caulfield Heath. He profiles well and expect a bold showing. Ditto from fellow debutant BOLTING BLUE (1), who looks good enough to deliver a running double for the Griffith yard. The jumpouts say he has plenty of ability and he looks ready to go. GLIDING LIGHTENING (11) resumes and has raced well in town. Placed on the synthetic her only start last preparation and won a recent Pakenham jumpout. In a leading barn and has race experience. TALLADEGA GIRL (13) resumes and is also in a smart stable. Pulled up with an issue when well supported at Sale on debut and has won two jumpouts. Carries a feater with the 4kg claim and that brings her right into it. CASUAL GHAI (2) has plenty up the sleeve and can show more freshened-up.
